ron-star and neutron-star--black-hole\nmerger is still expected for a fraction of the systems if the supernova kick\naligns favorably with the orbital motion. For double neutron star\n(neutron-star--black-hole) systems we estimate mergers in about $9 \\%$ ($1 \\%$)\nof cases while about $77 \\%$ ($94 \\%$) of binaries are disrupted, i.e.,\nsupernova kicks actually enable gravitational-wave mergers in our cases;\nhowever, we expect a reduction in predicted gravitational-wave merger events.\n(abbr.)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Nov 2021 19:10:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 12:23:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-09"}
