xistence of stationary heteroclinics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Nov 2021 15:29:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 31 May 2022 16:33:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-01"}
{"id":"2111.12547","submitter":"Ronghai Wu","authors":"Ronghai Wu, Lei Zeng, Xing Ai, Yunsong Zhao","title":"A modified divide-and-conquer based machine learning method for\n  predicting creep life of superalloys","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.mtrl-sci","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  Recently Liu et al. (Acta Mater., 2020) proposed a new divide-and-conquer\nbased machine learning method for predicting creep life of superalloys. The\nidea is enlightening though, the prediction accuracy and intelligence remain to\nbe improved. In the present work, we modify the method by adding a\ndimensionality reduction algorithm before the clustering step and introducing a\ngrid search algorithm to the regression model selection step. As a consequence,\nthe clustering result becomes much more desirable and the accuracy of predicted\ncreep life is dramatically improved. The root-mean-square error,\nmean-absolute-percentage error and relevant coefficient of the original method\nare 0.2341, 0.0595 and 0.9121, while those of the modified method are 0.0285,\n0.0196, and 0.9806, respectively. Moreover, the ad-hoc determination of\nhyperparameters in the original method is replaced by automated determination\nof hyperparameters in the modified method, which considerably improves the\nintelligence of the method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Nov 2021 15:29:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-25"}
